HEADWORD: Rhipidoglossa
<hw>Rhi*pi`do*glos"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/<?/<?/ a fan + <?/<?/<?/<?/ a tongue.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of gastropod mollusks having a large
number of long, divergent, hooklike, lingual teeth in each transverse
row. It includes the scutibranchs. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

